column9: # Prokka gives a gff file with a long header and with all the contigs at the bottom.  The command below keeps only the gff table.; ;         LN=`grep -Hn "^>" intermediary/prokka.gff | head -n1 | cut -f2 -d ":" || if [[ $? -eq 141 ]]; then true; else exit $?; fi`;         LN1=1;         LN=$(($LN-$LN1));         head -n $LN intermediary/prokka.gff | grep -v "^#" | sort | uniq | grep -v "^==" > intermediary/annotation.filt.gff
